        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Background: this paper studies the cholinergic synapse located in the superior cervical ganglion (SCG).\n\nFig.2: Without α3 expression, fast EPSPs are completely absent in sympathetic ganglia. This shows that the α3 subunit is part of the postsynaptic nACHR.. Experimental description: Tissues were of mouse species: \"A colony of α3 neuronal nAChR-deficient mice was maintained by breeding ..." ;
